        "special_abilities": [
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "Salamanders can cause any weapon they wield to deal half its damage as fire damage, and to become lethal and non-archaic. If the weapon already deals two damage types, this effect replaces one with fire. In addition, salamanders can grant weapons they wield the burn critical hit effect (1d4, 2d4 at CR 6, 3d4 at CR 11, and 3d4 at CR 16+). If the weapon has any other critical hit effects, the salamander chooses only one to apply on a critical hit.",
